  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why am I getting Likes from people in India when my ad campaign is targeted only to people in SF?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you're receiving Likes from people in India despite targeting your ad campaign specifically to individuals in San Francisco (SF). Here are some possibilities to consider:\n\n1. **Targeting Settings**: Double-check your targeting settings in the ad platform. Ensure that you're correctly set up to include only users in San Francisco and that there are no additional settings or audience overlaps that might allow users from other regions to see your ad.\n\n2. **VPNs and Location Spoofing**: Some individuals might be using VPNs to access the internet from different locations, making it appear as if they are in San Francisco when they are actually in India.\n\n3. **Global Reach**: Depending on the platform, your ads might still be shown to users who are outside your targeted area, especially if they share interests or behaviors relevant to your product or service.\n\n4. **Engagement from Friends or Family**: People who live in SF may have friends or family in India, and those individuals may be interacting with your ad through shares or likes.\n\n5. **Algorithmic Influence**: Social media algorithms sometimes show ads to users based on their behavior and interests rather than strictly where they live. This can result in unexpected engagement from users outside your targeted area.\n\n6. **Interest-Based Targeting**: If you used interest-based targeting alongside geographic targeting, it might have drawn in users from other regions who have shown similar behavioral patterns or interests.\n\n7. **Errors or Bugs**: There could be a technical issue or bug with the ad platform that is causing misattribution of likes or interactions.\n\nTo troubleshoot the issue, you can:\n\n- Review your ad settings and audience targeting options closely.\n- Analyze the demographics of the people liking your ad using insights and analytics provided by the ad platform.\n- Reach out to customer support of the advertising platform for clarification and assistance.\n\nBy examining these factors, you should be able to identify the cause of the issue and take appropriate action.",
